    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. I want to make sure the post doesn't sound like it's just ignoring obvious problems though. Some people say that without regulation, the internet just becomes a toxic mess of misinformation and harassment that drowns out actual discourse. How can I frame my argument to counter the idea that \"regulation is necessary for a healthy society\"?",
